cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on detecting dishonest users in online social networks, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
2. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper deals with the behavior of users in online social networks and how it affects the sales of a product, which falls under the scope of social and behavioral sciences. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a detection framework to identify dishonest users in OSNs, which involves security and cryptography. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents a set of fully distributed and randomized algorithms to detect dishonest users in OSNs, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses algorithms to detect dishonest users in OSNs, which falls under the scope of artificial intelligence.
